<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 02 at 5:07PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Pushmataha,
southwestern Latimer and southeastern Pittsburg Counties through 545
PM CDT...
At 507 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Stanley, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Clayton...                        Clayton Lake State Park...
Stanley...                        Higgins...
Kiamichi...                       Tuskahoma...
Yanush...                         Dunbar...
Sardis...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
